        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">What Orlando Fire Department Inspectors Look For</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">The Orlando Fire Department checks fire extinguisher compliance during routine commercial property inspections. Most common violations cited in Orlando:</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 mb-8"><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Expired tags in I-Drive hotel and resort properties — high-volume hospitality operations with multiple buildings and hundreds of units require systematic tracking</span></div><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Missing Class K extinguishers in hotel banquet kitchen and food service areas</span></div><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Humidity-induced dry chemical agent caking in extinguishers stored in outdoor or poorly ventilated locations</span></div><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Missing or inadequate coverage in theme park support facilities and warehouse-scale hospitality operations</span></div></div>

